Sometimes you have to wait for the right moment..and that wait is the hardest part ..
Beautiful sand dunes in Death Valley National Park, California.

The winds were crazy and I was trying to change to wide angle lens without the sand getting in the camera sensor.. so had to find the best place to change my lens safely and never imagined to witness this beautiful cloud and lit up perfectly at sunset

node.text:
When the mountains call you must go. 
••••
Thanks to our friend Sandra @nationalparkpatchlady for the Mt. Rainier adventure. 
•
Made a quick scouting trip with @timcooperphotography over the weekend.  Took a photo. 📷⁠
⁠
❓ ❓ ❓⁠
⁠
Did you know Mount Rainier last erupted about 1,000 years ago and is considered active? ⁠
⁠
📷 📷 📷⁠
⁠
Everyone stands in front of Reflection Lakes (including several 4x5 shooters) for the iconic shot. But if you walk down the road a bit toward Louise Lake, there are great spots right off the road with pretty wildflowers this time of year. ⁠
⁠
📍: Mount Rainier National Park, WA⁠
📅 : August 2021⁠
⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Park Geek® in Mount Rainier National Park with @npcapics. May be an image of nature, sky, tree and mountain.

node.text:
A year ago, the Great American Outdoors Act was passed and progress is being made at parks, monuments, memorials, battlefields nationwide to make them better and fix them up. We would like to thank the @npcapics for advocating for this bill and always championing for public lands. Here is to continued progress and improvements for public lands. 
——-
Thanks to our friends at NPCA @npcapics for working to have made this happen. 
•
After two decades of advocacy, thousands of Hill meetings, and hundreds of thousands of actions + messages from our supporters, today we celebrate the first anniversary of the passage of the Great American Outdoors Act 🎉🌲⛺️ The historic victory for parks authorized billions of dollars to fund critical maintenance and conserve vulnerable lands. 
-
Thanks to GAOA, you'll soon find upgraded campsites at @YosemiteNPS and @MountRainierNPS, a repaired base for @StatueEllisNPS, updated facilities at @RockyNPS, and much more. Learn more about the places GAOA is helping protect at the 🔗 in our bio. 
-
📸 Dennis Sabo 📍 Tipsoo Lake in Mount Rainier National Park
——-

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Park Geek® in Canyonlands National Park with @canyonlandsnps, @nic.sabine, and @cnhamoab. May be an image of nature and sky.

node.text:
The early bird catches the worm or at least the sunrise at Canyonlands. 
••••
Thanks to Nic @nic.sabine for sharing the shot and the experience. 
•
Sunrise at Mesa.
❗️
I put off getting this shot for a long time. I knew the legend of Mesa Arch, but I also knew that I wanted this shot in my portfolio. I spent all night at the arch shooting astro and waiting for the sunrise. It really is just as bad as people say; hundreds of people crowded around an arch no more than 20 ft wide, pushing and shoving to try to get one of the very few good vantage points. It’s something I’ll never forget, but also something I’ll never do again. 
📷
Nikon D750 | Tamron 15-30 2.8
